body:
This release is focused on improving the ClojureScript REPL support. Added `ClojureScriptBuild,figwheel {}` to configure figwheel-main options. These aren't used directly by Clojurephant, but are exposed over the tooling API for use by the [clojurephant-tooling](https://github.com/clojurephant/clojurephant-tooling) library in your REPL.

**build.gradle**

```groovy
dependencies {
  devImplementation("dev.clojurephant:clojurephant-tooling:0.1.0-beta.1") {
    capabilities {
      requireCapability("dev.clojurephant:clojurephant-tooling-figwheel-main")
    }
  }
}

clojurescript {
  builds {
    dev {
      figwheel {
        openUrl = "http://localhost:8000/index.html"
      }
    }
  }
}
```
In your REPL:

```clojure
(do (require '[dev.clojurephant.tooling.figwheel-main :as fig]) (fig/start :dev))
```

